Text.SourceString: Just call me <NPCName>Jack</>!//I run the local ranch.//Your lot has plenty of space to raise livestock. Once you’re settled, maybe we can discuss raising animals.
Having another rancher can be good for the local economy. We might be able to produce local cheese again.
I spend a lot of time at the ranch managing the shop’s supplies, making sure we have enough to sell.//That sort of thing.
Who are my customers? Ha. That’s tricky.//<portrait=normal>You, I guess. And neighboring ranchers.
I find cooking very relaxing… And, better yet, you get to eat the result!
I spend a lot of time at the ranch managing the shop’s supplies, making sure we have enough to sell.//That sort of thing.
Who are my customers? Ha. That’s tricky.//<portrait=normal>You, I guess. And neighboring ranchers.
I find cooking very relaxing… And, better yet, you get to eat the result!
I wash my hair every day. A habit, really, rather than a necessity.//<portrait=happy>Thankfully I don’t have that much hair, so it isn’t a big deal.
Over there… There’s a perfectly good creek down there.
When people buy animals from us, we usually ship them the next morning.//But since you live close by, we’ll walk them over right away.
Good customer service, isn’t it?
I join a yoga class every Saturday at the community center.//What do you usually do on the weekend?
How are you?
Don’t camp in this forest.//Listen to me on this.
I almost became somebody’s lunch, years ago, because I fell asleep by the creek.//<portrait=normal>Good thing, <NpcName>Kira</> was there to scare off the bear.
My body is very stiff… What am I doing wrong?//I’ve been doing yoga for so long now.
Oh, you do yoga too?//So tell me, <PlayerName>$player</>, what did I do wrong?
Don’t camp in this forest.//Listen to me on this.
I almost became somebody’s lunch, years ago, because I fell asleep by the creek.//<portrait=normal>Good thing, <NpcName>Kira</> was there to scare off the bear.
When people buy animals from us, we usually ship them the next morning.//But since you live close by, we’ll walk them over right away.
Good customer service, isn’t it?
Do you have enough fodder for the week, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I always say, it’s never bad to have extra.
You can place bee houses around the island.//They aren’t just limited to your farm… Um… <NpcName>Ben</> told me this.
No, I’ve never actually tried it myself.
What’s it like, anyway?//Moving to a different island and completely starting a new life?
Ah, never mind.//<portrait=concerned>It would be way too much work to transport all my animals… Not like I would ever have the guts to tell my parents about abandoning their ranch, anyway.
Take the path to the left. There should be a path toward the vineyard that leads to town.
I don’t think I should go to Starlet Town today.//I’m busy. Are you heading there?
Take the path to the left. There should be a path toward the vineyard that leads to town.
After all this time, <PlayerName>$player</>. It still confuses you, eh?
I assign myself a day off, usually on Saturdays.//I’m pretty strict about it.
Looking after my mental health, and all that jazz. You know?
Are you done working for the day?
If I weren’t a rancher like my dad, I would be a chef.
I like taking care of animals and cooking, but I prefer my animals.//<portrait=concerned>Besides, who else is going to do it?
<NpcName>Kira</> told me that something smelt really strong this morning. I can’t smell anything in the air.//<portrait=concerned>Hmm… That makes me nervous.
I should get my nose checked.
<NpcName>Kira</> told me that something smelt really strong this morning. I can’t smell anything in the air.//<portrait=concerned>Hmm… That makes me nervous.
Is it really that strong? I should get my nose checked.
So excited that you’re here! My first customer of the day.//Need anything?
Yoga always puts me in a good mood!
I am so energized!//A new man, if you will.
Walking is an excellent way to keep moving, but remember to push yourself every once in a while.
Heh… Why am I giving you fitness advice?
My wife is the expert if you need any information about cavern monsters.
She spent a lot of her adult years under there… Deep in the cavern.
Yoga always puts me in a good mood! I did a little bit of it this morning.
I'm so energized!//A new man, if you will.
I name the animals at the ranch after Summer crops. Melon, Poppy, Radish.
I think they’re beautiful names.//Not <NpcName>Betsy</>, <NpcName>Kenny</> named her that.
Cows produce milk every day when they’re healthy.
They do need to be mature first. Calves can’t produce milk.
Cows produce milk every day when they’re healthy.
They do need to be mature first. Calves can’t produce milk.
I have a meeting at the community center tomorrow after work.

Just me and a couple of friends. We’ll be sharing our weeks, and all that jazz.//<portrait=normal>Always welcome to stop by, <PlayerName>$player</>. We’ll be all ears… Consider this an open invitation.
You’re really going to tell me how to raise my cattle?//<portrait=happy>I’ve been doing this for who knows how long. And I am a rancher. But go off, I guess.
Oh yeah! That’s a good idea, actually.//<portrait=normal>You do need to brush them every day. Good tip.
<NpcName>Kira</> and I don’t really go out on weekdays. I like to watch TV or cook in the evening.
Have you watched this week’s cooking show?//They’re very informative, and you learn a new skill every time.
The ranch is old… Takes a lot to maintain.//It was my dad’s, and his dad’s before that.
<NpcName>Kira</> and I don’t really go out on weekdays.//I like to watch TV or cook in the evening.
Make sure to talk to your animals every day.//They may not speak the same language we do, but they understand.
Gah. I sounded like <NpcName>Kenny</> just now… That was weird.
Only the best grass for my fodder. Those animals are my friends.//Only the best for them!
I know they would do the same for me, if our roles were reversed.
Too bad you’re already settled in that cabin, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I would’ve rented you my charming old room.
Or is it an old, charming room? Either way, you get the gist.//<portrait=normal>The room is charming, and it’s old.
Only the best grass for my fodder. Those animals are my friends.//Only the best for them!
I know they would do the same for me, if our roles were reversed.
You’re really going to tell me how to raise my cattle?//<portrait=happy>I’ve been doing this for who knows how long. And I am a rancher. But go off, I guess.
Oh yeah! That’s a good idea, actually.//<portrait=normal>You do need to brush them every day. Good tip.
We’re not selling the ranch to Pufferfish.//It’s been in my family for many generations, and I hope that won’t ever change.
<NpcName>Kira</> and I don’t celebrate birthdays. It’s personal…
But don’t let that stop you from giving us gifts. Ha ha!
Cherry Blossom Festival is coming up.
I hope I don’t get sick before the beach cleanup this Saturday.
I’m feeling a bit under the weather.
Usually coops come with their own incubators. That way you don’t always have to buy chickens from us.//Save some of your hard-earned money, eh?
You can place an egg inside and wait a few days for it to hatch. Yeah, exactly! You get it, the usual.
I saw <NpcName>Taco</> in here the other day. He went inside the barn and played with the cows.
I saw <NpcName>Taco</> in here the other day. He went inside the barn and played with the cows.
The more you upgrade the fodder, the better quality your animal products will be.
Psst… There’s a pile of coconuts just behind the barn.
I’m trying to collect as many coconuts as possible before Summer ends.//I might go to the beach again tomorrow and see if I can get some more.
Usually coops come with their own incubators. That way you don’t always have to buy chickens from us.//Save some of your hard-earned money, eh?
You can place an egg inside and wait a few days for it to hatch. Yeah, exactly! You get it, the usual.
I had an apple for breakfast this morning.
Oh, that’s more than enough for me. I can’t overeat in the morning, or I would… Umm…
Never mind.
Fall is when we get busy, with cooking contest coming up.//A lot of preparation for me.
It’s probably your busiest season as well, huh?
Guess who’s back in town?
<NpcName>Ben</>. That kid just got back from his journey, doing who knows what.
I saw <NpcName>Taco</> in here the other day. He went inside the barn and played with the cows.
I saw <NpcName>Taco</> in here the other day. He went inside the barn and played with the cows.
It’s hard to get fresh vegetables during the Winter… Good thing we have some stocked up in the kitchen.//<portrait=concerned>But that won’t last us too long, I’m afraid.
It must be hard to enter the cooking contest with so few fresh options on hand.
Unless you have a well-stocked fridge, that is.
Are you farming this Winter, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Can you believe it’s the twenty-first already?
Can you believe it’s the twenty-fourth already?
I had an apple for breakfast this morning.
Oh, that’s more than enough for me. I can’t eat too much in the morning, or I would… Umm…
Never mind.
Make sure to let your animals out of the barn once in a while, okay?
Especially in such beautiful weather as this.
Make sure to let your animals out of the barn once in a while, okay?
Especially in such beautiful weather as this.
Have you fed your animals today?
It’s gloomy out. Our animals could use a little extra love… Just saying. No need to get defensive.
I’m just glad I’m still here to make sure the animals are dry and healthy.
Have you fed your animals today?
It’s gloomy out. Our animals could use a little extra love… Just saying. No need to get defensive.
Have you fed your animals today?
It’s gloomy out. Our animals could use a little extra love… Just saying. No need to get defensive.
If you and I are cold, it stands to reason that your pet might be cold too.
If you and I are cold, it stands to reason that your pet might be cold too.
I told <NpcName>Kenny</> that when I can’t do it anymore, he needs to be the one who takes care of these animals.
I don’t think I have anything to worry about. He’s a gentle soul, and those animals have special place in his heart.
Inhale the future, exhale the past.
I feel like it sounds a bit daunting when you tell yourself that you need to exercise.
Sometimes, after work, I just put some music on in the living room and dance with <NpcName>Kira</> instead.
Uh oh… I said too much.
Fancy seeing you here, <PlayerName>$player</>. Buying or selling?
I don’t shop here often, because we usually cook with fruit and vegetables from our garden.
But it’s raining today, so I figured I would just pick up some stuff here.
I think I’ll make some soup tonight. Nice and warm. Yum…
We keep piles of fodder in the back, in case there’s a drop in grass supply.
I think I’ll take a nap for a bit, after you leave.
I hear the mayor often visits businesses around the island. Keeping track and all that.//<portrait=concerned>But I’ve never once had one of these visits.
Do you think it’s because he trusts me more than other businesses?//<portrait=concerned>Or does he just forget because I live in the woods?
Ah, you’ve never had one of these visits either?//That makes me feel a tad better.
I keep an eye on the animals every single day.
Well, it’s actually <NpcName>Kenny</> who does that. Heh!
The extra room in the ranch is for rent, if you know someone who’s looking. Errr…
It leaks a bit in the rain, but it doesn’t rain that often here. So, no big deal.//But I thought I should mention it up front.
You get what you pay for around here, I guess.//The barn isn’t brand new anymore. So I can let the extra room go for dirt cheap.
I’m pretty sure these barns are listed in a library book somewhere, as some of the island’s oldest buildings.
Well, when else will you be able to say that you live in a historic building?
If you see <NPCName>Kenny</>, would you tell him to come to find me?//<portrait=concerned>He forgot to feed one of the cows.
I don’t mind him playing his flute, but he should get his work done first.
Are your animals doing okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?//We’ve got everything you need for them down at the ranch.
<NPCName>Kenny</> does all the work of caring for the animals, so there’s not much to do around here but sell supplies.
I don’t mind, though.//<portrait=normal>It gives me more time to check the shop’s inventory. Someone’s gotta do it, right?
You should never be rude to your animals.//They may not understand our language, but they can feel love.
One way is to make sure you talk to your animals every day.//Petting them is a great way to show love as well.
Are you doing okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Let me or <NPCName>Kenny</> know if you need anything.
*lost in thought*
Have you ever tried yoga? It’s a surprisingly good workout.//<portrait=surprised>Oh! You’re a yogi! No way!
<NPCName>Kira</> got me into yoga. It helps with stretching stiff muscles.//So, tell me, are all Pokyons into yoga, or just you?
I’m curious what stories people have told you about <NPCName>Kira</>.//My wife is a bit of a legend around here.
She used to camp out in caverns, back in the day.//<portrait=surprised>To clear out the ghouls and stuff.//<portrait=happy>I don’t know for sure. I’ve never been inside a cavern before.
I tried to cook a big dinner for the whole family last night.//<portrait=happy>If you heard <NPCName>Kenny</> shouting all the way over at your place, that was probably why.

I had no idea food could blow up like that! But it’s okay, though.//<portrait=happy>We’re all learning, am I right?//<portrait=normal>As long as we have fun and don’t give up. That’s the key to successful cooking.
It’s nice to walk slowly and take in all of the island’s sights.//There’s no reason to go too fast.
<NPCName>Kenny</>’s a daydreamer, but he has his head on straight.//He’s a good kid.//<portrait=happy>He’s also a good flute player… Just like his mother.
The ranch is closing early today, so make sure you get whatever you need quickly.
Do you need something from the ranch? It isn’t urgent, is it?//<portrait=normal>Oh, good! Then let’s just wait until tomorrow.
I should have done inventory last night, but I got caught up watching the cooking show.//<portrait=surprised>Wow! That show can hypnotize you for hours!

The vineyard? Hmm… Not really. I don’t really hang out there.//<portrait=concerned>Don’t really know the <NPCName>Walter</> guy that well either.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Kira</> knows his wife, though.
Part of running the ranch is selling items and keeping up with stock numbers.//<NPCName>Kenny</> would rather be out with the animals, so I handle the store part.
Do you prefer sweet or savory foods?//<portrait=surprised>I like them all… Kimchi, fruit tarts… ANY fruit tarts!
<NPCName>Kira</> isn’t a picky eater. I don’t think she loves or hates any particular foods.//She sure loves flowers, though.
Don’t worry about getting me anything for my birthday.//<NPCName>Kira</> and I don’t celebrate birthdays.
What did you do before you came to Coral Island, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Corporate folk, huh? That’s chill.//<portrait=normal>You must work in tall buildings, huh… I’m impressed.
You gave him cheese, huh? That’s too bad. I hope he wasn’t rude about it.//But yeah, <NPCName>Kenny</> doesn’t eat cheese, eggs… Things like that.
People have offered to help me count the supplies on the ranch, but I always turn them down.//It feels good to do it myself.
<NPCName>Kira</> said I ought to spend time at the Tavern making new friends.//She thinks it would be good for me.
I’m from here, so I know a lot of these folks already.//<portrait=normal>But I don’t know them as well as my parents do.

I’ll have to look for more animal feeds to stock.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Ben</> is helpful with this type of work.//<portrait=normal>He’s young and gathers feed quickly… Which is weird, ’cause he walks really slow.
Has <NPCName>Kenny</> taught you about animals’ moods yet?//I bet he has. So, your chickens and stuff will get upset if you don’t feed them.
<NPCName>Kenny</>’s such an eager beaver, that kid.//He’s been like that since he was a tiny blob.
Do you grow most of your own food?//I assume farmers do that.
Me, farming? No… Not for me.//Besides, who’s going to take care of my ranch if I farm?//<portrait=surprised>Hmm… Solid point, I do have <NPCName>Kenny</>.
It’s rough when rude customers come to the ranch.//It’s not everyone, or even most people. It’s just a few prickly individuals.
Oh! That’s what I was supposed to do yesterday. I completely forgot to get groceries.
Sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>, what did you say?
I like Spring. It’s easier to get fresh ingredients this time of year.//<portrait=surprised>Spring and Summer… And don’t forget Fall.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm… Hang on. That’s basically the whole year.
I should probably restock the ranch’s feed supply.//Everyone stocks up on feed in the Spring.
What are your favorite Spring veggies, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Cucumber fan, huh? Not bad, not bad!//<portrait=normal>I’ve always been a big fan of lettuce.

<NPCName>Jim</>’s son… What’s his name?//Yeah! <NPCName>Theo</>!//<portrait=surprised>I gave him some strawberries this one time, and he told me they were…crunchy.//<portrait=happy>Sure cracked me up!
I’m glad <NPCName>Kira</>’s not out hunting anymore.//Not that I don’t think she could handle it. It’s the heat!
I try and stick to shady areas on my way to work in the mornings.//<portrait=surprised>I might melt if I spend too much time in the sun.
People need to be careful when they let their kids swim in the ocean. I’ve heard some wild legends about what lives down there.//I won’t risk it.
Fall means harvest season, and harvest season means good food!//I can’t decide what to cook first!
This crisp Fall chill makes working outside easier.
It also makes <NPCName>Kenny</>’s flute go out of tune. Someone should probably tell him that.//<portrait=happy>Me? No… Maybe you should do it. You two are friends, aren’t you?
Fresh veggies are hard to come by in the Winter.//I might wait until Spring to try out new recipes again.
Have you stored up enough food for Winter?//It’s hard to cook if you don’t have the right ingredients.
Winter’s too cold to stay late at the ranch.//I usually go right home for a warm meal.
If you need a warm place to rest during your errands, come by the ranch.//I keep it nice and toasty in there.
Like humans, animals don’t like getting wet.//You should keep them inside on days like this.
If you’re looking for <NPCName>Kenny</>, he’s probably inside the house.
<NPCName>Kira</> never did mind going out in the rain. Me… I’m a little different.
Let’s talk another time. I need to get home.
Weather forecasting is such a sham sometimes.//<portrait=concerned>They said the rain would be over by now.
Hot meals are great on days when the weather’s bad.//What should I cook for dinner tonight?
I’m glad I’m not out in that rain.//My groceries can wait. I’m not going to Sam’s in this weather.
<PlayerName>$player</>, have you seen my coffee cup?//I swear I left it around here somewhere.
It’s time to make something hot to eat! What should I cook?
I hope this rain is over by morning.//It gets pretty muddy up around here.
I’ll have to do my yoga indoors this evening. It doesn’t look like the rain’s going to let up.
Make sure your animals are inside, <PlayerName>$player</>!
I need to get out of this before I get hurt.//Being struck by lightning is no joke.
Let’s talk another time. I need to get home.
*in a hurry*
I hope nothing gets damaged in this storm.//We can’t really afford to repair the ranch.
The storm is fine… As long as there’s no blackout.//<portrait=annoyed>Oh yeah, it’s happened, let me tell you. It’ll happen again.//<portrait=concerned>Yes, it will.
I hope this storm is over by morning.//It gets pretty flooded out there.
I’ll have to make something hot for dinner tonight.//Have any suggestions?
Let’s talk another time. I need to get home.
Snow’s thick today, huh?//At least it’s warm in here.
The town needs to get someone to shovel all the snow. It’s impossible to get around.
It feels weird to have guests, let me tell you.//<portrait=happy>In a nice way, though… Weird nice.
<NPCName>Kenny</>? Hmm… He’s either out at the ranch or in his room.
This old thing doesn’t look so bad, does it?//<portrait=happy>I’ve been taking good care of this building. Look around!

As a matter of fact, yes! I did use to live here. This was when I was a single man… Before I moved into <NPCName>Kira</>’s house.//<portrait=happy>In that happy little room right there. Neat, isn’t it?
<PlayerName>$player</>! It’s nice of you to visit. You’re welcome to stay for dinner if you want.//<portrait=normal>I’m making plenty!
There’s always something to be done around here.//That’s part of running a business.
Have you seen my coffee cup?//I know I set it down somewhere.
How do you organize your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>? You should tell me about it sometime.//We can trade organization tips.
<NPCName>Kira</> is better at this than I am.//You should find her if you need help with yoga poses.
Breathe in… Hold it… Breathe out.
